// art Kids On a bicycle Armenian Street Painted by Ernest Zacharevic. It depicts a little girl taking her younger brother on a bicycle ride. Boy on the Bike Ah Quee Street This mural on a side door shows boy hanging out on his motorcycle as he watches the traffic passing by along the street. He looks bewildered! The Old Fisherman Balik Pulau Mural by Julia Volchkova. Depicts an elderly fisherman who is seemingly involved in mending his net. The Silat Master Children in a Boat Chew Jetty Another portrait by Julia Volchkova , this time of a man performing Silat, a traditional martial art practised in both Malaysia and Indonesia. The mural depicts two children, a boy and a girl, playing on a berthed sampan by the shore, with a pet cat. Reaching Up Cannon Street Reaching Up depicts a little boy reaching for a hole in the wall, standing on a chair and inching himself as high as he could reach.
//food Char Kway Teow Siam Road The noodles come with a generous serving of pork lard, juicy cockles and smooth and savoury rice noodles. Assam Laksa Air Itam Market Food Court Mouth-watering sour, spicy and savoury soup, the tangy and sweet fish taste paired together with the fresh vegetables and mackerel will definitely leave you wanting more. Hokkien Prawn Noodles "CY Choy Road " The aromatic pork based soup is sweet and fresh and you can choose to top up additional ingredients like fish balls or pork innards. "Cendol" "Penang Road" The chilled coconut milk helps quench your thirst, and the green jelly strands and red kidney beans give the dessert a good bite. Nasi Kandar Bee Ghah Cafe Nasi Kandar is a dish of rice and various marinated meats and vegetables, drenched in curry gravy. Pasembur Padang Kota Lama Pasembur is a Malaysian salad consisting of cucumber, potatoes, beancurd, turnip, beansprouts, prawn fritters and other seafood and topped with a spicy peanut sauce. Nasi Lemak Sri Weld Food Court Rows of fragrant steamy coconut rice waiting for sweet spicy sambal sauce to be poured over. Choose between nasi lemak with chicken, fried fish, salted fish, shrimp and cuttlefish. Wanton Noodles Lebuh Chulia The noodles come drenched in a slick black sauce and garnished with bits of pork lard for that crunch factor. The noodles were springy and wantons were well seasoned. Oyster Omelette Bayan Baru Market Food Court Oyster Omelette is a dish of fried eggs, flour and juicy succulent oysters Curry Mee Jalan Air Itam " The curry is cooked over a charcoal stove and the curry is extremely fragrant!" Roti Canai Jalan Transfer Pair your roto canai with the aromatic chicken curry that is moderately spicy with fall of the flesh tender chicken meat. Lor Bak Trang Road Lor Bak are pork rolls made from minced pork and wrapped in beancurd skin before getting deep fried till they are crispy. Ikan Bakar Jalan Butterworth These fish are grilled over a wire topped charcoal and marinated with a delicious sauce.
//history Fort Cornwallis Jalan Tun Syed Sheh Barakbah Fort Cornwallis is a bastion fort in George Town, Penang, Malaysia, built by the British East India Company in the late 18th century. Cheong Fatt Tze Mansion Lebuh Leith The Cheong Fatt Tze Mansion is a government gazetted heritage building. The mansion\'s external decorations and indigo-blue outer walls make it a very distinctive building, and it is sometimes referred to as The Blue Mansion. Busy commercial area, surrounded by banks, cafes, colleges and eating shops. European mercantile and retail businesses spilled out of Beach Street into the eastern half of Bishop Street, whereas the western half of Bishop Street adjoining the more Oriental Pitt Street was home to a number of traditional Chinese trades. Bishop Street Clan Jetties Of Penang Pengkalan Weld Busy, scenic destination featuring a traditional village of rustic houses on stilts over the water. Queen Victoria Memorial Clock Tower Built to commemorate Queen Victoria\'s 1897 Diamond Jubilee, the tower is sixty feet tall, one foot for each year of Victoria\'s reign. Lebuh Light Penang State Museum and Art Gallery
The Penang State Museum and Art Gallery is a museum and art gallery in George Town, Penang, Malaysia. Penang War Museum Jalan Batu Maung The Penang War Museum is the largest war museum in Southeast Asia. It covers the now-defunct Batu Maung Fort, which was built by the British Army prior to World War 2. Pinang Peranakan Mansion The museum itself is housed within a distinctive green-hued mansion at Church Street, George Town, which once served as the residence and office of a 19th-century Chinese tycoon, Chung Keng Quee. Church St Leong San Tong Khoo Kongsi Cannon Square The Khoo Kongsi is a large Chinese clanhouse with elaborate and highly ornamented architecture, a mark of the dominant presence of the Chinese in Penang Kek Lok Si Temple Tingkat Lembah Ria 1 The Kek Lok Si Temple is a Buddhist temple situated in Air Itam, Penang, Malaysia. It is the largest Buddhist temple in Malaysia
// shop Gurney Paragon Mall Gurney Drive Gurney paragon is set to be the new premier shopping, entertainment, office and luxury residential address in Penang. Gurney Plaza Straits Quay Jalan Seri Tanjung Pinang Straits Quay is a place for leisure activities and it has over 100 shops, bistros, bars and boutiques to look out across the festive marina at the heart of Straits Quay. Prangin Mall " Jalan Dr Lim Chwee Leong" Prangin mall is 5 floors of compact low-cost bonanza and is the best place to shop for cheap clothes, shoes and accessories. 1st Avenue Penang Jalan Magazine Just across the road from Penang Times Square, KOMTAR and Prangin Mall on Jalan Magazine, 1st Avenue Plaza is a seven storey mall that offers fashion, leisure, a cinema and a slew of dining outlets for the style conscious urbanites living and working in Penang. "Queensbay Mall " Persiaran Bayan Indah Queensbay mall features 5 retail levels of international and home-grown brands and has more than 500 stores including fashion, lifestyle, dining, entertainment, sports, electronics, home furnishing and department store. Design Village Penang Jalan Cassia Barat 2 Design Village Penang has 150 stores set in a lush 24-acre tropical garden, which hosts a broad variety of exciting international and local brands, both premium and high street. Penang Times Square Jalan Dato Keramat Penang Times Square is a mixed development project comprising a mall, residential tower and office block. Komtar, the icon in Penang, frequently serves as an easily identifiable landmark for travellers exploring Georgetown. "M Mall 020 " "In M Mall 020, they have over 3000 stores catering to health, beauty, fashion and even electronic gadget stores. Visitors also get to enjoy a wide variety of dining options ranging from familiar favourites to new gastronomic experiences. "
